*Routes:**
```
/api/auth/**     → AUTH-SERVICE
/api/users/**    → USER-SERVICE
/api/movies/**   → MOVIE-SERVICE
/api/theaters/** → THEATER-SERVICE
/api/showtimes/**→ THEATER-SERVICE
/api/bookings/** → BOOKING-SERVICE
```

---

### 3.3 Auth Service

**Port:** 8085  
**Purpose:** Authentication and authorization  
**Database:** None (stateless)  

**Responsibilities:**
- User registration (via User Service)
- User login
- JWT token generation
- Token validation
- Password encryption (BCrypt)

**Key Endpoints:**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---------------|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Register new user | No |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | User login | No |
| GET | `/api/auth/validate` | Validate JWT token | Yes |

**Dependencies:**
- Calls User Service via Feign Client
- Uses BCryptPasswordEncoder for passwords
- Generates JWT with HS512 algorithm

---

### 3.4 User Service

**Port:** 8081  
**Purpose:** User profile management  
**Database:** `user_db`  

**Responsibilities:**
- User CRUD operations
- Profile management
- Role management (CUSTOMER, ADMIN, THEATER_OWNER)
- User activation/deactivation

**Key Endpoints:**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---------------|
| POST | `/api/users` | Create user | No* |
| GET | `/api/users/{id}` | Get user by ID | Yes |
| GET | `/api/users/email/{email}` | Get user by email | Yes |
| GET | `/api/users` | Get all users | Yes (ADMIN) |
| PUT | `/api/users/{id}` | Update user | Yes |
| DELETE | `/api/users/{id}` | Delete user | Yes (ADMIN) |

*Accessible from Auth Service for registration

**Database Schema:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    last_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    phone_number VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    role VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    is_active BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
```

---

### 3.5 Movie Service

**Port:** 8082  
**Purpose:** Movie catalog management  
**Database:** `movie_db`  

**Responsibilities:**
- Movie CRUD operations
- Search by title, genre, language
- Filter by status (NOW_SHOWING, COMING_SOON, ARCHIVED)
- Movie metadata management

**Key Endpoints:**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---------------|
| POST | `/api/movies` | Create movie | Yes (ADMIN) |
| GET | `/api/movies/{id}` | Get movie by ID | No |
| GET | `/api/movies` | Get all movies | No |
| GET | `/api/movies/status/{status}` | Get by status | No |
| GET | `/api/movies/genre/{genre}` | Get by genre | No |
| GET | `/api/movies/search?title={title}` | Search by title | No |
| PUT | `/api/movies/{id}` | Update movie | Yes (ADMIN) |
| DELETE | `/api/movies/{id}` | Delete movie | Yes (ADMIN) |

**Database Schema:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE movies (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    director VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    language VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    genre VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    duration_minutes INTEGER NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE NOT NULL,
    rating NUMERIC(3,1),
    cast TEXT NOT NULL,
    poster_url VARCHAR(500),
    trailer_url VARCHAR(500),
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
```

**Enums:**
- **Genre:** ACTION, COMEDY, DRAMA, HORROR, ROMANCE, SCI_FI, THRILLER, ANIMATION, DOCUMENTARY, FANTASY
- **Status:** COMING_SOON, NOW_SHOWING, ARCHIVED

---

### 3.6 Theater Service

**Port:** 8083  
**Purpose:** Theater and showtime management  
**Database:** `theater_db`  

**Responsibilities:**
- Theater CRUD operations
- Showtime scheduling
- Seat availability management
- Conflict detection for showtimes
- Seat reservation/release

**Key Endpoints:**

**Theaters:**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---------------|
| POST | `/api/theaters` | Create theater | Yes (ADMIN) |
| GET | `/api/theaters/{id}` | Get theater by ID | No |
| GET | `/api/theaters` | Get all theaters | No |
| GET | `/api/theaters/city/{city}` | Get by city | No |
| PUT | `/api/theaters/{id}` | Update theater | Yes (ADMIN) |
| DELETE | `/api/theaters/{id}` | Delete theater | Yes (ADMIN) |

**Showtimes:**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---------------|
| POST | `/api/showtimes` | Create showtime | Yes (ADMIN) |
| GET | `/api/showtimes/{id}` | Get showtime | No |
| GET | `/api/showtimes/movie/{movieId}` | Get by movie | No |
| GET | `/api/showtimes/theater/{theaterId}` | Get by theater | No |
| PATCH | `/api/showtimes/{id}/reserve?numberOfSeats={n}` | Reserve seats | Yes* |
| PATCH | `/api/showtimes/{id}/release?numberOfSeats={n}` | Release seats | Yes* |

*Called internally by Booking Service

**Database Schema:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE theaters (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    address VARCHAR(500) NOT NULL,
    city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    state VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    zip_code VARCHAR(6) NOT NULL,
    phone_number VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    total_screens INTEGER NOT NULL,
    is_active BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE showtimes (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    movie_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    theater_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    screen_number INTEGER NOT NULL,
    show_date_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    total_seats INTEGER NOT NULL,
    available_seats INTEGER NOT NULL,
    price_per_seat NUMERIC(10,2) NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
```

**Business Logic:**
- Prevents double-booking on same screen
- 3-hour buffer between showtimes (movie + cleanup)
- Real-time seat availability tracking

---

### 3.7 Booking Service

**Port:** 8084  
**Purpose:** Ticket booking and reservation management  
**Database:** `booking_db`  

**Responsibilities:**
- Create bookings
- Seat reservation coordination
- Payment status tracking
- Booking cancellation with seat release
- Multi-service orchestration

**Key Endpoints:**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---------------|
| POST | `/api/bookings` | Create booking | Yes |
| GET | `/api/bookings/{id}` | Get booking by ID | Yes |
| GET | `/api/bookings/reference/{ref}` | Get by reference | Yes |
| GET | `/api/bookings/user/{userId}` | Get user bookings | Yes |
| GET | `/api/bookings/showtime/{showtimeId}` | Get showtime bookings | Yes (ADMIN) |
| PATCH | `/api/bookings/{id}/confirm` | Confirm booking | Yes |
| PATCH | `/api/bookings/{id}/cancel` | Cancel booking | Yes |
| PATCH | `/api/bookings/{id}/payment?status={status}` | Update payment | Yes |

**Database Schema:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE bookings (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    booking_reference VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    user_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    showtime_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    movie_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    theater_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    number_of_seats INTEGER NOT NULL,
    total_amount NUMERIC(10,2) NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    payment_status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    booking_date_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    seat_numbers VARCHAR(500),
    special_requests TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
```

**Enums:**
- **BookingStatus:** PENDING, CONFIRMED, CANCELLED, COMPLETED
- **PaymentStatus:** PENDING, PAID, REFUNDED, FAILED

**Service Orchestration:**
```
Booking Creation Flow:
1. Validate User (via User Service)
2. Get Showtime details (via Theater Service)
3. Validate Movie (via Movie Service)
4. Check seat availability
5. Reserve seats (via Theater Service)
6. Create booking record
7. Return booking confirmation
```

---

## 4. Technology Stack

### 4.1 Backend Technologies

| Category | Technology | Version | Purpose |
|----------|-----------|---------|---------|
| **Language** | Java | 21 | Core programming language |
| **Framework** | Spring Boot | 4.0.2 | Application framework |
| **Cloud** | Spring Cloud | 2024.0.0 | Microservices infrastructure |
| **Service Discovery** | Eureka | 2024.0.0 | Service registry |
| **API Gateway** | Spring Cloud Gateway | 2024.0.0 | Routing and filtering |
| **REST Client** | OpenFeign | 2024.0.0 | Inter-service communication |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL | 15+ | Relational database |
| **ORM** | Hibernate/JPA | 6.x | Object-relational mapping |
| **Security** | Spring Security | 6.x | Authentication/Authorization |
| **JWT** | JJWT | 0.12.3 | Token generation/validation |
| **Validation** | Jakarta Validation | 3.x | Input validation |
| **Mapper** | MapStruct | 1.5.5 | DTO-Entity mapping |
| **Build Tool** | Maven | 3.9+ | Dependency management |
| **Documentation** | SpringDoc OpenAPI | 2.3.0 | API documentation |
| **Monitoring** | Spring Actuator | 4.0.2 | Health checks |

### 5.3 Authorization Matrix

| Endpoint | CUSTOMER | ADMIN | THEATER_OWNER |
|----------|----------|-------|---------------|
| **Movies** |
| GET /api/movies | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| POST /api/movies | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| PUT /api/movies/{id} | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| DELETE /api/movies/{id} | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Theaters** |
| GET /api/theaters | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| POST /api/theaters | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| PUT /api/theaters/{id} | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| DELETE /api/theaters/{id} | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Showtimes** |
| GET /api/showtimes | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| POST /api/showtimes | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| PUT /api/showtimes/{id} | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Bookings** |
| POST /api/bookings | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| GET /api/bookings/user/{userId} | ✅ (own) | ✅ (all) | ✅ (all) |
| PATCH /api/bookings/{id}/cancel | ✅ (own) | ✅ (all) | ✅ (all) |

### 5.4 Security Layers

**Layer 1: API Gateway**
- JWT token validation
- Rate limiting
- CORS configuration
- Request sanitization

**Layer 2: Service-Level**
- Gateway authentication filter
- Prevents direct service access
- Validates X-User-Id and X-User-Role headers

**Layer 3: Method-Level** (Future Enhancement)
- @PreAuthorize annotations
- Role-based access control
- Custom security expressions

### 5.5 Password Security

- **Algorithm:** BCrypt
- **Strength:** 10 rounds
- **Salt:** Automatically generated per password
- **Storage:** Never stored in plain text


### 6.3 Sample API Calls

#### Register User
```bash
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}
```

#### Login
```bash
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}
```

#### Create Movie
```bash
POST http://localhost:8080/api/movies
Authorization: Bearer {JWT_TOKEN}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Inception",
  "description": "A mind-bending thriller",
  "director": "Christopher Nolan",
  "language": "English",
  "genre": "SCI_FI",
  "durationMinutes": 148,
  "releaseDate": "2010-07-16",
  "rating": 8.8,
  "cast": "Leonardo DiCaprio, Marion Cotillard",
  "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg",
  "trailerUrl": "https://example.com/trailer.mp4",
  "status": "NOW_SHOWING"
}
```

#### Create Booking
```bash
POST http://localhost:8080/api/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {JWT_TOKEN}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "showtimeId": 5,
  "numberOfSeats": 2,
  "seatNumbers": "A1, A2",
  "specialRequests": "Wheelchair accessible"
}
```

---

**End-to-End User Journey:**

```bash
# 1. Register User
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "firstName": "Test",
    "lastName": "User",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
    "password": "Test@123"
  }'

# Save the token from response
TOKEN="eyJhbGciOiJIUzUxMiJ9..."

# 2. Browse Movies
curl http://localhost:8080/api/movies

# 3. Get Movie Showtimes
curl http://localhost:8080/api/showtimes/movie/1

# 4. Create Booking
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/bookings \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "userId": 1,
    "showtimeId": 1,
    "numberOfSeats": 2
  }'

# 5. Get My Bookings
curl http://localhost:8080/api/bookings/user/1 \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"
```